Governor Godwin Obaseki of Edo State has transmitted power to Deputy Governor Philip Shaibu in acting capacity as he proceeds on annual vacation.
Special Adviser to the Governor on Media Projects, Crusoe Osagie, in a statement, indicated that Governor Obaseki has written to the Edo State Assembly, notifying the House of the transmission of power to the deputy governor to act on his behalf while he proceeds on annual vacation.
